CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 3, reads: "Does This Condition Exist in Other Neighborhoods? Liquor Control Board Should Exercise Better Judgment - One of the overlooked evils in some neighborhoods of Allegheny County is the location of taverns in close proximity to churches, schools and playgrounds. Although such establishments do not operate on Sundays, their presence and the conduct of some patrons prove annoying during the week.... What Does 'License' Mean to Liquor Control Board? 1951 Liquor Laws Governing State Liquor Control Board - Sacred Heart Church...was Liquor Control Board aware of this in Braddock?"
TitMainTitle: Green Castle Bar and Sacred Heart Church, at intersection of Talbot Street, Braddock
